The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, February 28, 2004 				 SBI helpline for Gail 
 OUR CORRESPONDENTNew Delhi, Feb. 27: Worried over the uncertainties on the stock market, Gail has arranged State Bank of India (SBI) loans at a 7.25 per cent annual rate of interest for its employees to buy the companys shares. 																								SBI has agreed to provide loans of up to a maximum of Rs 2.5 lakh to an employee, depending on his or her grade. The loan is being made available to all regular employees on the rolls of Gail, including functional directors who have joined the company in regular pay scales. The maximum repayment period for the loan is 36 months and the EMI has been fixed at Rs 3,099 per lakh. There will be no pre-payment penalty and no processing fee required for the loan. Each employee can buy a maximum of 1200 shares at the minimum reserve price. 
